node.text:
Wild ride 🐎 Bareback riding is a form of horseback riding without a saddle. It requires skill, balance, and coordination, as the rider does not have any equipment to compensate for errors of balance or skill.

Proponents of bareback riding argue that riding in this fashion is natural, allows considerable communication with the horse, and improves a rider's balance. The drawbacks include a higher risk of injury due to an increased risk of falling off the horse, the potential to develop poor riding form, and the possibility of considerable discomfort to both horse and rider due to the absence of a supporting tree and any padding between the rider's seat bones and the horse's spine. Over time, it is more fatiguing to both horse and rider to ride bareback.

📽 @kerrikasem
🎶 Sting - Desert Rose (feat. Cheb Mami)
📍 Essaouira, Morocco

node.text:
Metamorphosis 🐸 🤯 🌍 

The process in which a tadpole turns into a frog is called metamorphosis, and it is an amazing transformation. Here @victorharold have broken metamorphosis down so you can see the stages a tadpole goes through as it develops into an adult.

Have you ever witness this in real life? Tag a @nature lover!

📽 @victorharold

node.text:
@dylanogline putting some good in the world by helping these incredible animals.
Elephants have endured rapid population decline, losing more than 86% of their numbers in just the past three decades. #WorldElephantDay was August 12th and YOU can help make a difference.
How you can help:
🐘 Make a donation: support elephant conservation by donating to a charity of your choice. @dylanogline supports @elephantcrisisfund
🐘 Educate yourself: Learn more about the threats facing elephants.
🐘 Spread the word on social media: share this post or create your own.
#animals #nature #animal #wildlife #love #cute #travel #photography #naturephotography #photooftheday #animallovers #wildlifephotography #instagood #animalphotography #love #photography 
#picoftheday
